cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.CY, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on social network analysis and privacy concerns related to it. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the potential use of these techniques by security agencies, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the difficulty of computing an optimal solution, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the potential for oppressed activist groups to conceal their existence, which could fall under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
